reviews.review_text: Need More!!!!!!!! C'mon folks, theres got to be more of this out there, truckin, nobody's, phil solo, phil and billy...feelin' groovy jam etc...some of best 8 minutes i've heard....Iowa City heads have been begging for this for years....help us!!!

What the!!? Phil's sound is awesome! What is going on with the stereo of his bass. It sounds like he has some strings panned left and some right. Anyone know?

Like Craw said, this is a great fragment. Wish there was more.

I know! Arc-12 asked about the stereo sound of Phil's bass. 
When they used the wall of sound each string (back then he only played a 4 string alembic i believe) was wired to a different row of bass speakers so the sound would come from different areas. The better recording were able to capture this phenomenon.
why god, oh why? doesn't more of this circulate?  this fragment is hot enough i had to turn up my air conditioner.  do yourself a favor and listen to this bit of phil through a pair of headphones.

Crispy treble & Crunchy bass. David's tape of the night. A rendom pick that's going stay in my tape player for a long time!!-------I've always loved "Playing in the jam". ----- Read my review for Feb 21,1992, the "So Many Roads" rehursal,

GDH This was played at Jerry Garcia's Memorial at DGP on 08/13/95. It was selected along with the Spectrum 09/21/72 Dark Star & several choice cuts selected by David Gans & Dick Latvala RIP. It remains one of my all time favorite jams. Check out Dicks Picks 28 the jazzy jamming style is similar to this. Isn't graet to be a Deadhead?

Takes me back I haven't heard this Phil jam in years until tonight. Back when I used to tape the Grateful Dead hour every weekend, this was one of the faithfully rewound highlights.

Must Listen This Jam leads into Sugar Mag and there is a copy available somewhere, I've got it.
Jamsonly If you have a copy of this show that has more than whats available here, you're in possession of something pretty rare. You should share it/upload it.

30 days of the dead released more of this as referenced below, there is a more complete version of this, but it was released only as mp3 by dead.net in their '30 days of dead' thing a few novembers ago.   

this is one of my favorite pieces of GD music.  don't forget to click on "check for other copies" and listen to the playin from set one.

The Phil Zone Ha! I call this jam "The Phil Zone" (putting that well-known Deadhead expression to good use!)....a nice long protracted bass solo that really highlights the stereo effects he had on that bass and the Wall of Sound; not sure I've ever heard it demonstrated so clearly on a soundboard (or anything else!).  Very cool!  If you didn't know better, you might think that a second bass was joining him for certain bass chords.  Definitely make sure you're sitting in the middle of the speakers when you listen to this one.

I need the trucking into Eyes then sugar mags Incredible playing seems to only be available in aud  is there a SBD available? Dying to get SDB at least of this fragment.  In eyes they quickly drop what was the standard outro jam and then go into space with Phil then pounding and a feeling groovy jam  Trucking into nobody's fault amazing too.  Incredible inventive playing shows you how good these guys were in all of 1973.   Now can I get a SBD please please if anyone is listening?
